id: pm-y4z5
title: pm get --full omits children for Plan parents while pm list --parent returns them
description: The full get projection does not expose child summary or rows for a Plan item even when live parent relationships exist and the list parent filter finds them.
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[7]: "area:graph","area:query",bug,children,plan,projection,sdk-parity
created_at: "2026-07-13T22:07:55.014Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-14T03:11:21.920Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-14T03:11:21.057Z"
author: codex-root
estimated_minutes: 180
acceptance_criteria: "A focused sandbox test reproduces Plan parent children and fails before the fix; Public SDK get/read primitives compute children consistently for Plan, Epic, Milestone, Feature, and custom parent-capable types rather than hard-coding container types; CLI human, JSON, TOON, MCP, and SDK projections report the same total and active child counts with deterministic bounded samples and explicit truncation metadata; pm list --parent and pm get --full parity is covered for open, closed, canceled, custom-type, missing-parent, and large child sets; The fix does not require a full tracker scan when the derived parent index is available and remains bounded at one million items"
parent: pm-6x7o
risk: medium
confidence: high
reporter: codex-root
severity: medium
environment: pm-cli 2026.7.13 on main 5194806d; Node v26.4.0; Linux; real repository tracker
repro_steps: "1. Create or select a Plan with items whose parent field is the Plan ID. 2. Run pm get <plan-id> --full --json and inspect .children. 3. Run pm list --status all --parent <plan-id> --no-truncate --json. Reproduced with pm-a8zm: get returned children:null while list returned pm-p9a4, pm-qnl2, and pm-lnrk."
resolution: Added a public bounded type-agnostic child projection; CLI auto-projects container-oriented built-ins and custom types while built-in leaf reads require explicit children projection and avoid corpus scans.
expected_result: "Full get and its public SDK contract expose a deterministic bounded child summary for every valid parent item type, including Plan, with total and active counts plus truncation or continuation metadata; CLI human and JSON projections agree with list --parent."
actual_result: "Item-prefixed root projections now use the same normalized field path as validation: item.children returns the bounded rollup, item.schedule.* filters the requested schedule keys, and item.claim_state.* includes claim context. Focused 19-test and linked 26-test matrices pass; full coverage is 5657/5657 at 100/100/100/100."
component: get query projection and SDK read primitives
regression: false
customer_impact: Agents using get as the canonical context call cannot discover executable tasks nested below a Plan and may incorrectly infer the plan has no children.
