comments[8]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-13T22:07:55.014Z",codex-root,"Duplicate check 2026-07-13: exhaustive all-status searches for get full Plan children,list parent mismatch,and child count found historical Plan and parent-filter work but no issue tracking this projection inconsistency; live reproduction is attached."
  "2026-07-13T22:45:36.051Z",codex-root,"Implementation evidence: get children are now type-agnostic and derived from the light indexed metadata path, with status totals, active count, deterministic id-sorted sample, sample_limit, truncation, next_offset, continuation command, and explicit one-million-row safety bound. Empty leaf rollups stay omitted unless explicitly requested for token efficiency."
  "2026-07-14T00:09:46.665Z",codex-gpt5,"Implementation evidence: rich get now uses a public type-agnostic child projection with summaries, bounded samples, continuation metadata, custom-type support, and a one-million-row safety ceiling. Plan and custom-parent regressions pass; exact-tree strict gates and 5656-test 100/100/100/100 coverage pass."
  "2026-07-14T00:29:10.605Z",codex-root,"Final verification: pm linked tests pass 44 focused executions across the child/history matrix with sandbox context parity; packed PmClient get reports children.count=1; full coverage 5656/5656 at 100/100/100/100."
  "2026-07-14T00:45:21.351Z",codex-root,Greptile review e72e80d9-93c1-4a1b-93cb-0f4799552240 found standard/deep get invokes the child corpus scan for leaf item types. Reopened to preserve type-agnostic parent support without adding O(n) work to ordinary leaf reads.
  "2026-07-14T01:01:50.089Z",codex-root,"Review-fix evidence: normal built-in leaf reads now bypass the workspace corpus loader; an explicit children field still projects any item type, while Plan and other container-oriented built-ins plus custom types retain automatic summaries. Direct loader-spy regression, empty Plan, bounded SDK projection, and all linked tests pass; full coverage is 5656/5656 at 100/100/100/100."
  "2026-07-14T03:06:37.498Z",codex-root,"Hosted Greptile exact-head review at 7261948b found a reproduced P1 field-projection bug: validateGetFields normalizes item.children and item.schedule.*, but fieldsIncludeRoot tests raw fields, so accepted item-prefixed root projections are silently omitted. Reopening the canonical rich-get projection owner before editing."
  "2026-07-14T03:11:20.161Z",codex-root,"Hosted-review remediation evidence: normalizeGetField now drives item field projection, root inclusion, and nested schedule filtering. Direct regressions cover item.children with non-empty rollup, item.schedule.start_at, and item.claim_state.claimed. ESLint, focused 19 tests, sandboxed linked 26 tests, and full 5657-test coverage at 100/100/100/100 pass."
