close_reason: "Fixed Greptile P1 by normalizing item-prefixed root and nested projections; exact regressions, linked tests, and full 100% coverage pass."
body: "## Live reproduction\n\npm get pm-a8zm --full --json | jq '{children}'\n=> {children: null}\n\npm list --status all --parent pm-a8zm --no-truncate --json | jq '{count,items:[.items[].id]}'\n=> count 3; pm-p9a4, pm-qnl2, pm-lnrk.\n\nThe three task records each persist parent: pm-a8zm and validation reports no dangling or parent-cycle issue.\n\n## Design expectation\n\nChild discovery is a graph-read primitive, not an Epic-only presentation convenience. The SDK should expose a bounded total, active count, status breakdown, deterministic sample, and continuation link or cursor for any parent-capable item. CLI, MCP, and packages should adapt that same result.\n\n## Safety\n\nTests must use sandboxed PM_PATH and PM_GLOBAL_PATH and cover both indexed and indexless fallback behavior."
